title: The Gold Rush
overview: A prospector goes to the Klondike in search of gold and finds it and more.

title: Queen
overview: A Delhi girl from a traditional family sets out on a solo honeymoon after her marriage gets cancelled.

title: Interstate 60: Episodes of the Road
overview: Neal Oliver, a very confused young man and an artist, takes a journey of a lifetime on a highway I60 that doesn't exist on any of the maps, going to the places he never even heard of, searching for an answer and his dreamgirl.

title: Nebraska
overview: An aging, booze-addled father makes the trip from Montana to Nebraska with his estranged son in order to claim a million-dollar Mega Sweepstakes Marketing prize.

title: Hunt for the Wilderpeople
overview: A national manhunt is ordered for a rebellious kid and his foster uncle who go missing in the wild New Zealand bush.

title: Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas
overview: An oddball journalist and his psychopathic lawyer travel to Las Vegas for a series of psychedelic escapades.
stars: ['Johnny Depp', 'Benicio Del Toro', 'Tobey Maguire', 'Michael Lee Gogin']

title: Almost Famous
overview: A high-school boy is given the chance to write a story for Rolling Stone Magazine about an up-and-coming rock band as he accompanies them on their concert tour.

title: The Grand Budapest Hotel
overview: A writer encounters the owner of an aging high-class hotel, who tells him of his early years serving as a lobby boy in the hotel's glorious years under an exceptional concierge.

title: The Martian
overview: An astronaut becomes stranded on Mars after his team assume him dead, and must rely on his ingenuity to find a way to signal to Earth that he is alive.

title: The Muppet Movie
overview: Kermit and his newfound friends trek across America to find success in Hollywood, but a frog legs merchant is after Kermit.

title: The Treasure of the Sierra Madre
overview: Two Americans searching for work in Mexico convince an old prospector to help them mine for gold in the Sierra Madre Mountains.

title: The Bridge on the River Kwai
overview: British POWs are forced to build a railway bridge across the river Kwai for their Japanese captors, not knowing that the allied forces are planning to destroy it.

title: The Big Short
overview: In 2006-2007 a group of investors bet against the US mortgage market. In their research they discover how flawed and corrupt the market is.

title: The Great Escape
overview: Allied prisoners of war plan for several hundred of their number to escape from a German camp during World War II.

title: Back to the Future Part II
overview: After visiting 2015, Marty McFly must repeat his visit to 1955 to prevent disastrous changes to 1985...without interfering with his first trip.
stars: ['Michael J. Fox', 'Christopher Lloyd', 'Lea Thompson', 'Thomas F. Wilson']

title: The African Queen
overview: In WWI Africa, a gin-swilling riverboat captain is persuaded by a strait-laced missionary to use his boat to attack an enemy warship.

title: Ed Wood
overview: Ambitious but troubled movie director Edward D. Wood Jr. tries his best to fulfill his dreams, despite his lack of talent.

title: The Intouchables
overview: After he becomes a quadriplegic from a paragliding accident, an aristocrat hires a young man from the projects to be his caregiver.

title: Barry Lyndon
overview: An Irish rogue wins the heart of a rich widow and assumes her dead husband's aristocratic position in 18th-century England.

title: Big Fish
overview: A frustrated son tries to determine the fact from fiction in his dying father's life.
